# Goal Description

Fix the Firebase Authentication issues, overhaul the Prompt Generator page using the three-layer system (Intent Inference, Blueprint, Generation), and host the application using Firebase Hosting.

## Proposed Changes

### Firebase Auth Fix

#### [MODIFY] [server.js](file:///f:/PROMPTLAB/src/server.js)
- Update Content-Security-Policy (CSP) headers in `helmet` configuration to allow scripts from `https://www.gstatic.com` and connections to `https://*.googleapis.com`. This fixes the issue where Firebase Auth scripts are blocked from loading on [login.html](file:///f:/PROMPTLAB/public/login.html) and [index.html](file:///f:/PROMPTLAB/public/index.html).

### Prompt Generator Improvements

#### [MODIFY] [Index / UI](file:///f:/PROMPTLAB/public/index.html)
- Redesign the generator UI to match the analyzer's quality.
- Remove the explicit "Task Intent" input field; the system will infer intent automatically from the core prompt.
- Add components for visualizing the Prompt Blueprint before final generation.
- Ensure a single "Generate" button functionality.

#### [MODIFY] [Engine / Service] (and [public/js/app.js](file:///f:/PROMPTLAB/public/js/app.js))
- Wire up the existing three-layer generation system ([generatorService.js](file:///f:/PROMPTLAB/src/services/generatorService.js) via [promptlab-engine.js](file:///f:/PROMPTLAB/public/js/promptlab-engine.js) bundle) to the frontend.
- Display the Intent Inference and Prompt Blueprint steps visually before final Generation.
- Ensure the analyzer scoring loop is active and functioning to auto-improve the generated prompt.

### Hosting

#### [NEW/MODIFY] Firebase Configuration
- Ensure `firebase.json` and `.firebaserc` are configured to deploy the `public` directory to Firebase Hosting.
- Run `firebase deploy` to host the site.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- N/A (Using browser subagent for end-to-end testing).

### Manual Verification
1. Run local dev server (`npm run dev`).
2. Use the browser to open `http://localhost:3000/login.html` and verify that the Firebase scripts load without CSP errors.
3. Test signing up and signing in with a test account.
4. Go to the Generator page and paste a simple prompt. Click "Generate" and verify the three-layer process (Intent -> Blueprint -> Final Prompt) works correctly and looks visually appealing.
5. Deploy to Firebase using `firebase deploy` and verify the live URL works.
